n=\\\\\\\"01:21\\\\\\\" data-source-html=\\\\\\\" • Source:\\\\n\\\\n CNN\\\\n \\\\\\\" data-fave-thumbnails=\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\"big\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"uri\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://media.cnn.com/api/v1/images/stellar/prod/iran-2-20260305105157873.jpg?c=16x9\\\\\\\" }, \\\\\\\"small\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"uri\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://media.cnn.com/api/v1/images/stellar/prod/iran-2-20260305105157873.jpg?c=16x9\\\\\\\" } }\\\\\\\" data-vr-video=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\" data-show-html=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-byline-html=\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\" data-timestamp-html=\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n Updated Mar 5, 2026, 11:29 AM ET\\\\n\\\\n PUBLISHED Mar 4, 2026, 12:34 PM ET\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\" data-check-event-based-preview=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-is-vertical-video-embed=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\" data-network-id=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-publish-date=\\\\\\\"2026-03-05T10:50:56.555Z\\\\\\\" data-video-section=\\\\\\\"world\\\\\\\" data-canonical-url=\\\\\\\"https://www.cnn.com/cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-branding-key=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-video-slug=\\\\\\\"cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-first-publish-slug=\\\\\\\"cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-video-tags=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-breakpoints=\\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\"video-resource--media-extra-large\\\\\\\": 660}\\\\\\\" data-display-video-cover=\\\\\\\"true\\\\\\\" data-details=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\">\\\\n\\\\nCNN's Frederik Pleitgen is on his way to Iran’s capital, Tehran, as Israel and the US continue their aerial campaign against the country. CNN is operating in Iran only with government permission.\\\\n\\\\\\\" data-check-event-based-preview=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-network-id=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-publish-date=\\\\\\\"2026-03-05T10:50:56.555Z\\\\\\\" data-video-section=\\\\\\\"world\\\\\\\" data-canonical-url=\\\\\\\"https://www.cnn.com/cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-branding-key=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" data-video-slug=\\\\\\\"cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-first-publish-slug=\\\\\\\"cnn-enters-iran-ldn-digvid\\\\\\\" data-video-tags=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\" class=\\\\\\\"video-resource\\\\\\\">\\\\n\\\\n Video Ad Feedback\\\\n\\\\n CNN enters Iran as conflict with US and Israel widens\\\\n\\\\n 1:21\\\\n\\\\n • Source:\\\\n\\\\n [CNN](https://www.cnn.com/)\\\\n\\\\n 1:21\\\\n\\\\n The Middle East\\\\n\\\\n [See all topics](/follow)\\\\n\\\\n Facebook\\\\n\\\\n Tweet\\\\n\\\\n [Email](mailto:?subject=CNN%20content%20share&body=Check%20out%20this%20article%3A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2026%2F03%2F04%2Fpolitics%2Freachout-iran-us-potential-talks)\\\\n\\\\n Link\\\\n\\\\n Threads\\\\n\\\\n Link Copied!\\\\n\\\\n Follow\\\\n\\\\n Iranian intelligence has sent word to the United States it could be prepared to open talks on how to end [the war](https://www.cnn.com/world/live-news/iran-war-us-israel-trump-03-04-26), according to people familiar with the indirect messages, but US officials say there are no negotiations underway and that potential “off-ramps” are unlikely to materialize in the near term.\\\\n\\\\n The messages were conveyed through a third country to the CIA, the people familiar said. But so far, it does not appear the channel has resulted in any serious discussions on how to bring the war to an end.\\\\n\\\\n Instead, American officials have described entering [a new, more intensive phase](https://www.cnn.com/world/live-news/iran-war-us-israel-trump-03-04-26?post-id=cmmc21jz500003b6tjbnge0rb) of the joint operation with Israel to degrade Iran’s missile program and ensure it not be able to obtain a nuclear weapon. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said during a briefing Wednesday the US was “just getting started.” And lawmakers who were [briefed by the administration](https://www.cnn.com/2026/03/04/politics/us-air-defenses-iran-attack-drones-challenge) Tuesday on Iran said they did not hear a distinct endgame, including potential efforts at diplomacy.\\\\n\\\\n Iranian leaders, for their part, haven’t demonstrated public willingness to negotiate as their ranks grow slimmer as a result of Israeli attacks.\\\\n\\\\n Yet the messages, however preliminary, do suggest an eventual pathway exists to brokering an end to the war. CNN has reached out to the CIA for comment. [The New York Times](https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/04/us/politics/trump-iran-intelligence-leaders.html) first reported on the messages from Iran.\\\\n\\\\n American officials insist they have not been in talks — either directly or through a third party — with the Iranians since nuclear negotiations fell apart days before the war began. They have, however, received messages from other countries offering to help defuse the conflict.\\\\n\\\\n “Since this\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"7ccd58866742112b\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n  \\\"warning\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"cb9a842055b05d6a\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Fetch\\\\n---\\\\nResponse body truncated after 2000000 bytes.\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"cb9a842055b05d6a\\\\\\\">>>\\\"\\n}\"}],\"status\":\"success\",\"toolUseId\":\"tooluse_VgH6rNrJMMqmC6VO8xyFPD\"},{\"content\":[{\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://edition.cnn.com/2026/03/04/politics/missiles-weapons-stockpile-iran-us-war\\\",\\n  \\\"finalUrl\\\": \\\"https://edition.cnn.com/2026/03/04/politics/missiles-weapons-stockpile-iran-us-war\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": 200,\\n  \\\"contentType\\\": \\\"text/html\\\",\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"24e557f0fc504e1e\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Fetch\\\\n---\\\\nHow many missiles do Iran and the US have? The war’s troubling munitions math | CNN Politics\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"24e557f0fc504e1e\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n  \\\"extractMode\\\": \\\"markdown\\\",\\n  \\\"extractor\\\": \\\"readability\\\",\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_fetch\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"truncated\\\": true,\\n  \\\"length\\\": 15000,\\n  \\\"rawLength\\\": 14229,\\n 